node LOS · LOS · ⟦THE LOSS OF IDEAS:LOS:097624⟧

WHO   — THE LOSS OF IDEAS — a polemos sphere — conflict & strategy
WHAT  — Ideas do not only get stolen; they get lost — burned, banned, forgotten, or simply never copied before their last keeper died. The Library of Alexandria is the symbol, but the real loss is quieter and vaster: techniques whose makers took the method to the grave, books erased on purpose, whole bodies of knowledge that fell through the gap between one generation and the next. The defence was always the same: copy it, and copy it again.
WHERE — the field of conflict — from the dawn of writing  Framework inputs: strife; the word; the might; the idea  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Ideas do not only get stolen; they get lost — burned, banned, forgotten, or simply never copied before their last keeper died. The Library of Alexandria is the symbol, but the real loss is quieter and vaster: techniques whose makers took the method to the grave, books erased on purpose, whole bodies of knowledge that fell through the gap between one generation and the next. The defence was always the same: copy it, and copy it again.
HOW   — Crystallized from the public record.

